And while they were doubting in Galilee, Jesus said to them, "The Son of Man is about to be delivered into the hands of men."
"Then they will kill him, and on the third day he will rise." They were extremely distressed. Temple tax.
And when they came to Capernaum, those who received the temple tax came to Peter and said, "Does your teacher not pay the temple tax?"
He said, "Yes." When Jesus entered the house, he went ahead of him, saying, "What do you think, Simon? From whom do the kings of the earth take toll or tax, from their children or from strangers?"
Peter said to him, "From strangers." Jesus said to him, "Then the sons are free."
But so as not to arouse their suspicions, go to the sea and throw out a line; and the fish that comes up first, take it. And when you open its mouth, you will find a stater. Take it and give it to them for me and for you."
